The paper discusses the behavior of agents in multi-agent complex systems, specifically in the context of two-player games and the automated synthesis of reliable controllers for reactive systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions mathematical frameworks and formal concepts, indicating that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-categories.
